Boeing has announced the opening of applications for a six-month paid business internship programme targeted at university students in Kenya. The internship will run from January to July next year. Applications are open until June 30, 2017. The International Business Internship Programme (IBIP) is open to all students studying in business-related fields including; Industrial Engineering, Accounting, Finance, Human Resources, Marketing, Strategy, Management, and Information Systems. &ldquo;The students will be provided with paid US-based work experience, which we are confident will prove extremely valuable when they return and invest their new skills to the benefit of Kenya,&rdquo; said Boeing Sub-Saharan Africa Managing Director, Mr Joao Miguel. Applicants must be enrolled in an undergraduate or graduate programme or have graduated within the last 12 months.